HEADWORD: Subatom
<hw>Sub*at"om</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
hypothetical component of a chemical atom, on the theory that the
elements themselves are complex substances; -- called also
<altname>atomicule</altname>.</def> <-- Add subatomic particles --
protons, neutrons, gluons, quarks, etc. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

